---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services | Hana Code Corp"
  description="What Hana Code Corp does: app development, Canadian financial tools, and our approach to building software."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="section hero">
      <h1>What We Do</h1>
    </section>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>App Development</h2>
        <p>
          We design, build, and maintain consumer applications focused on
          financial planning and personal productivity. Our apps are built
          natively for iOS and the web, with an emphasis on clarity, performance,
          and privacy.
        </p>
        <p>
          From concept through launch and ongoing maintenance, we handle every
          stage of the product lifecycle. Our apps are available through the
          the web, with mobile apps coming soon.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Canadian Financial Tools</h2>
        <p>
          We specialize in building tools for the Canadian financial landscape.
          Canada has a unique system of registered accounts, government benefits,
          and tax rules that most financial software ignores or gets wrong.
        </p>
        <p>Our apps understand and properly model:</p>
        <div class="features">
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Registered Accounts</h3>
            <p>
              RRSP contribution room, TFSA limits, and the tax implications of
              withdrawals from each account type.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Government Benefits</h3>
            <p>
              CPP and OAS eligibility, timing optimization, and how benefit
              amounts change based on when you start receiving them.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Canadian Tax Rules</h3>
            <p>
              Federal and provincial tax brackets, OAS clawback thresholds, and
              tax-efficient withdrawal ordering strategies.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Non-Registered Accounts</h3>
            <p>
              Capital gains treatment, dividend tax credits, and how
              non-registered investments interact with registered accounts in
              retirement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Our Approach</h2>
        <div class="features">
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Privacy First</h3>
            <p>
              Financial data is sensitive. We design our apps to keep your data
              on your device wherever possible. We never sell your information to
              third parties.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Canadian-Built</h3>
            <p>
              Every feature is designed specifically for Canadian tax law and
              retirement systems. No adapting American tools — built from the
              ground up for Canada.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Clear Design</h3>
            <p>
              Complex financial concepts presented through clean, intuitive
              interfaces. We make the complicated feel simple without
              oversimplifying the results.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Continuous Improvement</h3>
            <p>
              Tax laws change. Contribution limits update. Government benefit
              rules evolve. We keep our apps current with regular updates so your
              projections stay accurate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Technology</h2>
        <p>
          We build with modern, proven technologies: React, TypeScript, and
          Swift for native iOS development. Our founder holds patents in
          adaptive scrolling for medical imaging and distributed image rendering
          architectures — a background in solving complex technical problems
          that informs everything we build.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our apps are designed for performance, accessibility, and reliability.
          We test thoroughly across devices and screen sizes to ensure a
          consistent experience for every user.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card cta-card">
        <h2>See Our Work</h2>
        <p>
          Explore our current projects and see how we put these principles into
          practice.
        </p>
        <a href="/projects" class="btn">View Projects</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: 6rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 4rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .card {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .card:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .feature {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding-top: 4rem;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
